<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1428,1822]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Remarks: The presence of this species in North America needs confirmation. 
<bibRefCitation author="Christiansen &amp; Bellinger" box="[1074,1436,1617,1642]" firstAuthor="Christiansen" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="1 - 1042" refId="ref75828" refString="Christiansen, K. &amp; Bellinger, P. (1980) The Collembola of North America, North of the Rio Grande, 1 st edition. Part 1. Poduridae &amp; Hypogastruridae, Part 2. Onychiuridae &amp; Isotomidae, Part 3. Entomobryidae. Grinnell College, Grinnell, Iowa, 1 - 1042." type="book chapter" year="1980">Christiansen &amp; Bellinger (1980)</bibRefCitation>
believed that Nearctic records of the species “have to be 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christiansen &amp; Bellinger" authorityYear="1980" box="[785,833,1654,1677]" class="Entognatha" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="essa">
<emphasis box="[785,833,1654,1677]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">essa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gisin" authorityYear="1952" box="[870,948,1654,1677]" class="Entognatha" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ripperi">
<emphasis box="[870,948,1654,1677]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">ripperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg" bookContentInfo="126 pp." box="[974,1157,1653,1678]" firstAuthor="Fjellberg" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Scandinavica, Suppl. 21" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref77798" refString="Fjellberg, A. (1985) Arctic Collembola. I. Alaskan Collembola of the families Poduridae, Hypogastruridae, Odontellidae, Brachystomellidae and Neanuridae. Entomologica Scandinavica, Suppl. 21, 126 pp." title="Arctic Collembola. I. Alaskan Collembola of the families Poduridae, Hypogastruridae, Odontellidae, Brachystomellidae and Neanuridae" type="book" year="1985">Fjellberg (1985)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christiansen &amp; Bellinger" authorityYear="1980" box="[1292,1374,1654,1677]" class="Entognatha" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="essa">
<emphasis box="[1292,1374,1654,1677]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. essa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Fjellberg" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="Macnamara" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[357,486,1690,1713]" class="Entognatha" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pannosa">
<emphasis box="[357,486,1690,1713]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. pannosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Babenko" bookContentInfo="336 pp." box="[500,746,1689,1714]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Babenko" journalOrPublisher="Chernova N. M. (Ed.), Nauka, Moscow" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref71839" refString="Babenko, A. B., Potapov, M. B., Stebaeva, S. K. &amp; Chernova, N. M. (1994) Opredelitel kollembol fauny Rossii i sopredelnykh stran. Semeistvo Hypogastruridae. Chernova N. M. (Ed.), Nauka, Moscow, 336 pp. [in Russian]." title="Opredelitel kollembol fauny Rossii i sopredelnykh stran. Semeistvo Hypogastruridae" type="book" year="1994">
Babenko 
<emphasis box="[607,664,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
(1994)
</bibRefCitation>
speculated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christiansen &amp; Bellinger" authorityYear="1980" box="[928,1010,1690,1713]" class="Entognatha" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="essa">
<emphasis box="[928,1010,1690,1713]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. essa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Fjellberg" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="Macnamara" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[1025,1154,1690,1713]" class="Entognatha" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pannosa">
<emphasis box="[1025,1154,1690,1713]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. pannosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christiansen &amp; Bellinger" authorityYear="1980" box="[1216,1312,1689,1714]" class="Entognatha" family="Hypogastruridae" genus="Hypogastrura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="devia">
<emphasis box="[1216,1312,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. devia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may all be junior synonyms of the widespread 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krausbauer" authorityYear="1898" box="[563,697,1725,1750]" genus="Achorutes" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species" species="assimilis">
<emphasis box="[563,697,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. assimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Some of these opinions are based on the study of extant 
<typeStatus box="[1370,1432,1726,1750]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">types</typeStatus>
, while others rely on morphological similarities and need further investigation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1428,1822]" box="[204,730,1797,1822]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">General distribution: considered cosmopolitan.</paragraph>
